RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Edmonds, WA operates under a mayor-council government. Mayor Mike Rosen took office on January 1, 2024, with his term expiring on December 31, 2027. The City Council consists of seven members elected at-large to four-year terms. The listed council members are based on the current information available on the City of Edmonds official website. While recent election results from November 2025 indicate Erika Barnett was elected for Position 3, new terms typically begin in January of the following year, so Neil Tibbott is listed as the current Council Member for Position #3.
